{[%csl Rb2,Rb3,Rb4,Rb5][%cal Gb8b2,Gg7b2,Ge8c7] THE MANEUVER ...NE8-C7 Very
often White tries to close the b-file by means of a2-a4 followed by Nb5. In
such a case, Black usually employs the manoeuvre...Ne8-c7 in order to exchange
the b5-knight (take a look at the diagram). After the exchange of the knights,
Black can start playing on the b-file which is already weakened by the move
a2-a4. In some positions, when the pawn is on a2, Black can consider playing ..
.Ne8-c7-b5-d4. Nevertheless, I have decided to focus on the idea of exchanging
the b5-knight since we can often see this approach in the theoretical part of
the database.}  *

