{[#] The situation is similar to the game Banusz - Turzo. Black's next move
would be ...c5-c4. Therefore, White went for the thematic} 20. Nd1 {[%cal
Gf3d2,Gd1e3,Ge3c4] Contrary to the above-mentioned game, this time, Black is
well coordinated. Therefore, with a precise play, he should create a decent
counterplay.} Qa3 $2 {This is already a mistake. After the exchange of the
queens, White manages to achieve his queenside blockade.} ({Better was to
insist on ...c5-c4 by playing} 20... Nb6 {[%cal Gc5c4] A possible line would be
} 21. Qd2 Qa3 22. Qe1 c4 23. Nd2 cxb3 24. axb3 Nd7 $44 {With a good
compensation for the pawn.}) 21. Qxa3 Rxa3 22. Nd2 {[%cal Gd2c4]} Nb6 23. Ne3 {
White managed to hold the c4-square. His position is almost winning already.}
Rd4 24. Nec4 Nxc4 25. Nxc4 Ra6 26. f4 {Since the queenside is already stable,
White can start expanding in the centre. Black does not have compensation
for the pawn.} Kf8 27. e5 Bg7 28. Rcd2 Rxd2 29. Rxd2 Ke8 30. exd6 exd6 31. Re2+
Kd7 32. Kf3 Ra8 $4 33. Nb6+ 1-0

