{PLAYING IN THE CENTRE AND ON THE KINGSIDE As the reader might have noticed by
now is not independent. In most of the cases, White starts playing in the
centre and on the kingside only after restricting Black's queenside play.
Sometimes, however, it is impossible to prevent Black's queenside counterplay.
In such cases, energetic play on the other wing or in the centre is required.
I illustrate these cases with two model games.}  *

