{ [#]Black is planning to establish a powerful knight on d3 after the
advance ...c5-c4. Therefore, White should play energetically.} 19. f4 $1 Nd7
20. f5 $6 {You should always be careful the advance f4-f5. Black can now make
use of the e5-square.} ({Instead, White should have gone for the thematic} 20.
e5 $1 dxe5 21. f5 {In this way, White strikes on the kingside without giving
the e5-square. Moreover, in some cases, White can use the e4-square to
transfer his knight to the kingside. Black has no satisfactory defence since
his pieces are concentrated on the queenside. A possible line would be} Qa6 22.
Nab5 gxf5 ({Closing the kingside with} 22... g5 {does not work either. After}
23. h4 gxh4 24. d6 exd6 25. Rxd6 Qb7 26. Bxh6 $18 {White has a mating attack.})
23. Rxf5 Qg6 24. Rf3 $18 {[%cal Gf3g3] White's attack is already decisive.
Black is helpless against the threats Rg3 and d5-d5 which can be executed in a
different move order.}) 20... Ne5 21. fxg6 fxg6 22. Bf4 {[%csl Re6][%cal Gf4e5,
Ge2g4,Gg4g6,Gg4e6] This was the point behind 20.f5. After eliminating the
knight, White can follow with Qg4, thus making use of the vulnerable kingside.
Black, however, has an important resource at his disposal:} c4 $1 {Once again,
this typical Benko idea gives Black counterplay. Besides freeing the c5-square
for the queen, Black also prepares the move ...Nd3. The critical position
arises after} 23. Bxe5 Qc5+ 24. Kh1 Bxe5 25. Qg4 {It seems that Black is about
to collapse. It turns out, however, that the powerful bishop is holding the
position.} Nd3 $2 {This is the decisive mistake after which White is winning
by force.} ({Black should have played} 25... Kh7 26. Rf7+ Bg7 $132 {when the
position remains unclear.}) 26. Nxc4 $1 {It is important to deflect Black's
queen from the important a7-g1 diagonal.} Qxc4 ({In the event of} 26... Nf2+
27. Rxf2 Qxf2 28. Nxe5 dxe5 29. Qxg6+ Kh8 30. Qxh6+ $18 {White has already
collected 4 pawns for the exchange. At the same time, White has a crushing
attack.}) 27. Qxg6+ Bg7 28. Rf7 Qd4 29. Rxd3 Rxc3 30. bxc3 Rxa4 31. Rdf3 Ra1+
32. Rf1 1-0

