$18) 19. Na5 Qc7 20. Qf3 Ra7 21. Nc4 $16 {White enjoys complete domination.})
15. Nc4 Qc7 16. Qg4 g6 17. Rae1 $1 {[%cal Gf2f4,Gf4f5] The e4-pawn is already
protected and White is planning to follow with the advance f2-f4-f5.} Nc6 18.
f4 Nd4 19. f5 {Black's position is very dangerous. In a practical game, it is
almost impossible to hold. The correspondence game that we have been following
went} Bf6 20. fxe6 fxe6 21. e5 dxe5 22. Bxd4 exd4 23. Qxe6+ Kg7 24. Nb6 Rad8
25. Nd7 Rxd7 26. Bxd7 d3 27. Kh1 $16 {So far, everything has been forced.
Black's position remains very difficult. Of course, we should take into
account that a computer might hold it. 1/2 (86) Kishkin, S (2387)-Beyer, U (2416)
ICCF email 2014} *

